Catclock is a modified version of the classic X11 xclock with support
for an additional "cat mode". In this mode, the clock displays an
animated cat with moving eyes and a swinging tail, inspired by the
Kit-Cat clock.

The program can also display time in analog and digital formats,
similar to the original xclock. It is lightweight and uses standard
X Toolkit libraries, making it suitable for minimal X11 environments.

This SlackBuild builds the program as "catclock" to avoid conflicts
with the system xclock binary.

This SlackBuild was generated as a starting point and must be reviewed
and adjusted before use or submission.
